cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is about comparing convolutional and recurrent networks for sequence modeling, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP) and speech processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). However, the paper also discusses the use of convolutional networks for tasks such as image captioning and audio synthesis, which are related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses empirical evaluation to compare the performance of different architectures, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
